# Analysis of Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
The structure consists of 9 building blocks arranged in 4 distinct layers:
- Layer 1 (Bottom): 1 yellow horizontal rectangular block
- Layer 2: 2 orange vertical cylindrical blocks
- Layer 3: 1 yellow horizontal rectangular block
- Layer 4: 2 blue cubic blocks
- Layer 5 (Top): 1 red house-shaped block with an archway and 2 orange triangular roof pieces

## Spatial Relationships
- The base is a yellow horizontal rectangular block
- Two orange cylindrical pillars stand vertically on the yellow base, spaced apart
- A second yellow horizontal rectangular block sits on top of the cylinders, forming a platform
- Two blue cubes sit side by side on top of the yellow platform
- A red house-shaped block with an archway sits on top of the blue cubes
- The house has an orange triangular roof composed of two angled pieces

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

Based on the analysis, I need the following blocks from the dictionary:
1. Block #8: Yellow horizontal rectangular block (used twice)
2. Block #10: Orange vertical cylinder (used twice)
3. Block #5: Blue cube (used twice)
4. Block #2: Red block with arch facing right/front
5. Block #14: Orange triangular sloped block (left side of roof)
6. Block #16: Orange triangular sloped block (right side of roof)
